    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require publishers to declare AI content on cover of books",
        "additional_details": "We think with the advent of AI it will become very difficult for human author to get a publishing contract. Yet, there is nothing to stop publishers writing books using AI, conjuring a human name for the \"author\" and selling it as a genuine work of art.\r\n \r\nI am asking that you make it law that if a publisher or printer writes a book in part or whole using AI; they have to declare the usage on the cover, including the percentage of AI written material.\r\n",
        "background": "Ensure that publishers printing and selling books written using artificial intelligence declare, on the cover, that AI was used and include the percentage of AI written material.",
